  • Class
    Description
    Module
    Singular unit which assists in the control of motion throughout the competition field, which provides implementation for control of both an azimuth (Rotation) motor, which controls the angle or direction of the module, and a linear (translation) motor which controls the velocity or magnitude of the module.
    Module.Constants
    Describes a given Module's measured constants that cannot otherwise be derived through its sensors and hardware.
    Module.ReferenceType
    Describes a given Module's current state of control, and how it should operate given the mode.
    ModuleStatusContainer
    Loggable input reference to a specific singular unit which assists in the control of motion throughout the competition field.
